WEBVTT

00:00:03.439 --> 00:00:11.039
I've escaped from the camp of Israel, many have fallen and died, even Saul, and his son Jonathan have died.

00:00:11.039 --> 00:00:16.440
How do you know, I stood above him, and put him to death?

00:00:16.440 --> 00:00:55.380
Teach all of our people this good, for Saul and Jonathan.

00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:03.420
Saul and Jonathan, you loved and cherished during your life.

00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:16.819
How the mighty have fallen, and the weapons of war have perished.

00:01:19.689 --> 00:01:24.290
Not once did David mention Saul's hurtful acts.

00:01:24.290 --> 00:01:33.290
To David, the assassination of Saul was an unrighteous act, and David could never rejoice over that.
